{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "25", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "07", "M": "31", "S": "35"}}, "news": [{"title": "Goa: GIDC allots three plots for ambitious IT park project", "para": "Goa's Verna industrial estate is set to host the 'Hello World Innovation & Research Park,' with three of its six large plots already allocated to a Mumbai-based developer. This ambitious project, expected to create 20,000-30,000 jobs, aims to attract skilled professionals back to the state.  The developer has sought clarity on infrastructure timelines, raising concerns about potential delays impacting project commencement.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/goa-government-allocates-land-for-major-it-park-20000-jobs-expected/131982358?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-235538/131982358.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Uttar Pradesh government to set up 500 GCC units by 2031: CM", "para": "Uttar Pradesh is positioning itself as India's next major hub for Global Capability Centres and technology investments. Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath invited global firms to \"build the future in Uttar Pradesh,\" highlighting a skilled workforce, improved infrastructure, and investor-friendly policies. The state aims for 40 million sq ft of office space and 500 GCC units by 2031, securing over Rs 50,000 crore in investment commitments during a recent dialogue.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/uttar-pradesh-government-to-set-up-500-gcc-units-by-2031-cm/131982268?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-75007/131982268.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "Tenants told to shift from illegal PGs and guesthouses by June 30 in Gurugram", "para": "Gurugram residents in illegal paying guest accommodations, guesthouses, and commercial establishments operating from residential plots in DLF Phases 1-5 have been urged to find new housing by June 30. The Town and Country Planning department is cracking down on violations of zoning and building norms. Many occupants were unaware of prior notices to property owners, prompting this public advisory to prevent inconvenience from sealing actions.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/gurugram-tenants-ordered-to-vacate-illegal-pgs-and-guesthouses-by-june-30/131982218?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2656445/131982218.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}